  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed advertisement would represent an incongruous visual intrusion to the street scene and contribute to an unsightly proliferation and clutter of signage and street furniture in the local area that would detract from the visual amenity of the street scene and harm the setting of the adjacent South Shoreditch Conservation Area. As such, the proposal would be contrary to policies D4 (Delivering Good Design) and HC1 (Heritage conservation and growth) of the London Plan (2021) and policies LP1 (Design quality and local character), LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) and LP7 (Advertisements) of Hackney&#x27;s Local Development Plan (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
